00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, D.C.

00:00:22.620 --> 00:00:24.630
&gt;&gt; Talía Guzmán-González:
Bienvenidos.

00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:30.520
Good afternoon and welcome
to the Library of Congress.

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:32.940
My name is Talía Guzmán-González,

00:00:32.940 --> 00:00:35.440
and I am a reference librarian
[inaudible] Brazilian specialist

00:00:35.440 --> 00:00:37.390
in the Hispanic division.

00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:40.620
On behalf of the Chief
of the Hispanic division;

00:00:40.620 --> 00:00:42.470
Doctor Georgia Dorn
[phonetic] it is my honor

00:00:42.470 --> 00:00:48.550
to welcome this distinguished group
of poets from around the world

00:00:48.550 --> 00:00:51.480
to the Maratón de Poesía.

00:00:51.480 --> 00:00:55.430
The Poetry Marathon or
Maratón de Poesía is led

00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.960
by its energetic leader
and poet in chief,

00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:05.630
Rei Berroa who is celebrating along
with the poets the 25th anniversary

00:01:05.630 --> 00:01:11.010
of this important event that I
learned, has been taking place

00:01:11.010 --> 00:01:14.600
at the Library of Congress
since 2001.

00:01:14.600 --> 00:01:17.150
So, we hope that this
partnership continues

00:01:17.150 --> 00:01:19.630
for many years to come, for sure.

00:01:19.630 --> 00:01:22.420
I'm going to briefly
introduce Rei Berroa and then,

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:25.350
I'm going to give him the
floor to introduce the poets

00:01:25.350 --> 00:01:28.250
and lead the rest of the event.

00:01:28.250 --> 00:01:31.610
Rei Berroa was born and raised
in the Dominican Republic

00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:34.960
and after traveling, learning
and consuming culture and poetry

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:37.250
from around the world,
he pursued a PHD degree

00:01:37.250 --> 00:01:39.000
at the University of Pittsburgh.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:43.890
He currently teaches contemporary
Spanish and Latin American culture,

00:01:43.890 --> 00:01:47.330
literature and literary theory
in the Department of Modern

00:01:47.330 --> 00:01:51.530
and Classical Languages at
George Mason University.

00:01:51.530 --> 00:01:55.770
He has published over 45 books
of poetry, literary criticism,

00:01:55.770 --> 00:01:57.870
anthologies and translations

00:01:57.870 --> 00:02:04.710
in several countries throughout
Latin America, Europe, India.

00:02:04.710 --> 00:02:06.440
So, all around the world.

00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:08.940
Please join me in welcoming
Rei Berroa and the poets

00:02:08.940 --> 00:02:10.740
to the Maratón de Poesía.

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:20.340
[ Applauses ]

00:02:20.340 --> 00:02:24.020 position:56%
